<br>
Silvery Belt of Contention - AC:10 +4 STA +5 WIS +5 INT - 21% Haste<br>
Shissar Scaled Gauntlets - AC:12 +5 WIS +5 INT +40 HP +40 Mana<br>
________________________________________________________<br>
Total Stats - AC:22 +4 STA +10 WIS +10 INT +40 HP +40 Mana - 21 % Haste<br>
<br>
VS. <br>
<br>
Silver Chitin Hand Wraps - AC:10 +3 STR +3 AGI +3 DEX +3 to all saves - 22% Haste<br>
Axegoreth's Belt of Defense - AC:20 +15 STR +15 WIS<br>
__________________________________________________________<br>
Total Stats - AC:30 +18 STR +15 WIS +3 AGI +3 DEX +3 to all saves - 22 % Haste<br>
<br>
<br>
Now, you just have to compare.  Just remember that if you went with the SCHW combo you could sell that other belt (goes for like 10k on my server) buy SCHW (down to like 4k now on my server) and sell the shissar guants (1k on my server I think) and use the 6 - 7k for other upgrades.  Personally, I'd take the 1% more haste, the 8 extra AC and the 5 extra raw wis.  The saves are an added bonus as well.  Hope this little comparison helps some.  <br>
<br>
<br>
It's not really the rarity of the belt (seen 2 drop while killing there with my main) it's the group you need to camp it.  Usually I went with a high level shaman, cleric and enchanter.  Those 4 arms can be nasty if you get a couple together especially you get a SK type and a cleric type in the same pull. hehe.  However, the benefits to others that come is usually a bit of exp, plus centi weapons, spells and the chance at a nice earring that sells for 4k on my server and is pretty good for melees, the belt, a couple nice neck items and a nice caster range slot item.  Plenty of good stuff for melee though there (belt, earring, centi weapons and shrouded medallion).  As a matter of fact I plan on going back once I get my BL up a little more and try to get one for him soon.  =P<br>
